    {
      "question": "Are ENERGY STAR rated shingles available in dark colors?",
      "answer": "Yes, many dark shingle colors meet ENERGY STAR standards for steep-slope roofs, which require initial solar reflectance of at least 0.25 and aged reflectance of 0.15. Popular ENERGY STAR certified dark colors include charcoal gray, estate gray, weathered wood, driftwood, pewter gray, and hunter green. Major manufacturers like TAMKO, Owens Corning, CertainTeed, and GAF offer extensive dark color selections with ENERGY STAR ratings and cool roof technology. These shingles use advanced infrared-reflective pigments and specially engineered ceramic-coated granules that reflect heat while maintaining dark color appearance. The key is that infrared radiation (heat) and visible light (color) are different wavelengths — modern technology reflects infrared while absorbing visible light to create dark colors. This means shingles can LOOK dark but DON''T ACT dark thermally. When shopping for dark shingles, specifically request ENERGY STAR rated products with cool roof technology and verify the Solar Reflectance Index (SRI). These products may qualify for federal tax credits, utility rebates, and insurance discounts while providing the aesthetic benefits of dark colors without energy penalties."
